main event: A civilian observed a hovering object resembling a star over the ocean for about 10 minutes on March 29, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as white and the size of a pinhead.,It was visible for ten minutes before disappearing behind a cloud.,The report suggests it could be a high and blinking star.,There were indications of red and blue flashes noted in other reports related to UFO sightings in the area.,The observer was a 22-year-old mailman who seemed intelligent.
sighted object: a star-like object hovering over the ocean
